HEADWORD: Asteridea
<hw>As`ter*id"e*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>'asteri`as</grk> + <ets>-oid</ets>. See
<er>Asterias</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A class of
Echinodermata including the true starfishes. The rays vary in number and
always have ambulacral grooves below. The body is star-shaped or
pentagonal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

